Solution.d2p1:Description: The Business Infrastructure "sub-solution" supports the RSA Archer Enterprise Management solution. It provides a central repository of business oriented assets including Products/Services, Business Processes, Information Assets, Facilities and Contacts.
Solution.d2p1:Name: Business Infrastructure

Solution.d2p1:Description:
RSA Archer Policy Management provides a consistent process for managing the lifecycle of corporate policies and their exceptions. The solution offers a centralized infrastructure for creating policies, standards and control procedures and mapping them to corporate objectives, regulations, industry guidelines and best practices. It also allows you to communicate policies enterprise-wide, track acceptance, assess comprehension and manage exception requests.

Through RSA Archer Policy Management, you can:

  • Centralize and normalize corporate policies.

  • Utilize the pre-loaded Archer GRC Content Library, which offers best-practice policies, control standards and procedures, authoritative sources and assessment questions.

  • Rationalize policies and standards by mapping them to corporate objectives and authoritative sources, such as PCI, ISO/IEC, COBIT, FFIEC, HIPAA, NIST and privacy legislation.

  • Document control procedures for operational risk and compliance activities.

  • Use automated workflow to ensure proper review and approval of all policy content before publication.

  • Communicate new and updated policies through user-specific dashboards and email notifications that are relevant to specific roles, departments and business functions.

  • Promote policy awareness through targeted training campaigns to identify and track gaps in policy comprehension and acceptance.

  • Initiate and manage requests for policy exceptions using built-in workflow and alert notifications.

  • Use real-time reports and dashboards to display policies and control standards mapped to regulatory requirements, identify gaps between policies and authoritative sources, and monitor policy exceptions.
Solution.d2p1:Name: Policy Management

Solution.d2p1:Description:
RSA Archer Compliance Management provides an access-controlled environment for automating enterprise compliance processes, assessing deficiencies and managing their remediation. The solution allows you to document process and technical controls, perform risk-based scoping, execute design and operating tests, maintain continuous controls monitoring and respond to identified gaps. You can also report assessment results and remediation activities to senior management and regulators through status and results dashboards. The solution is designed to automate compliance processes for Sarbanes-Oxley sections 302 and 404, J-SOX, Gramm-Leach-Bliley, and other requirements and standards.


Through RSA Archer Compliance Management, you can:

  • Document your control procedures and test plans, mapping them to applicable control standards, regulations, business units, risks, business processes and technologies.

  • Determine which controls need to be tested during a given assessment period through risk-based scoping.

  • Manage control self-assessments and design and operating tests for process controls, which include general computer controls, authorizations, reconciliations, completeness checks, etc.

  • Perform continuous controls monitoring by capturing the results of automated configuration checks via pre-built integration with leading scan technologies.

  • Deliver manual assessments to device and application owners for technology baselines that cannot be evaluated through scan technologies.

  • Inform testers of their work queues via rules-driven email notifications and a "My Tasks" list on role-specific home pages.

  • Generate deficiencies automatically for non-compliant control activities, and map those findings to policies, regulations and risks.

  • Route findings to appropriate personnel, who can resolve them through remediation tasks or exception requests.

  • Create remediation plans that relate multiple findings, and track actual and estimated remediation costs and timeframes.

  • Form a consolidated picture of compliance efforts and remediation processes through reports and dashboards.

  • Integrate compliance management data and processes into your risk management and corporate governance initiatives.
Solution.d2p1:Name: Compliance Management

Solution.d2p1:Description: The Issue Management solution provides users with the ability to identify and assign responsibility for the gaps, issues and deficiencies identified by their risk and compliance program.  Users document these items in the Findings application, which is preconfigured with the relationships to various components of the eGRC platform, including risks, questionnaires, policies and authoritative sources.  This solution also contains two applications that enable users to manage their response to identified findings.  Remediation Plans allows users to document and assign responsibility for corrective actions that address Findings.  Exception Requests allow users to grant temporary acceptance of an identified risk.
Solution.d2p1:Name: Issue Management

Solution.d2p1:Description: This solution contains the pre-built Compliance Questionnaires that are part of the Compliance Management solution.
Solution.d2p1:Name: Compliance Assessments

Solution.d2p1:Description:
La administración de riesgo de RSA Archer le permite identificar riesgos, evaluar su probabilidad e impacto, relacionarlos con controles de mitigación y rastrear la resolución. Puede desarrollar un repositorio de riesgos de reputación, financieros, operacionales y de TI; conectar dichos riesgos a objetivos corporativos, métricas de soporte y eventos de pérdida, y entregar evaluaciones de riesgo objetivo para evaluar riesgos identificados en el ambiente. Adicionalmente, puede administrar la corrección o aceptación de conclusiones de evaluación.

Con Administración de riesgo de RSA Archer, puede:

  • Crear un registro de posibles riesgos y relacionarlos con objetivos corporativos, indicadores clave de riesgos y controles de mitigación.

  • Mantener un repositorio de métricas cualitativas, cuantitativas y de comercio, y automatizar la recopilación de datos de soporte.

  • Documentar y administrar eventos de pérdida que representen riesgo financiero para el negocio.

  • Crear evaluaciones dinámicas en línea para evaluar riesgos en el ambiente utilizando una biblioteca de preguntas relacionadas con declaraciones de posible riesgo, fuentes autorizadas y estándares de control.

  • Iniciar campañas de evaluación en línea y notificar automáticamente a los asesores sus tareas y fechas de vencimiento.

  • Puntuar automáticamente evaluaciones, que calcula calificaciones de riesgo inherente que identifican áreas de problemas que requieren un esfuerzo de corrección prioritario.

  • Generar conclusiones para cada pregunta respondida incorrectamente, enrutándolas automáticamente al personal que corresponde.

  • Calcular automáticamente el riesgo residual según las puntuaciones de evaluación y las actividades de mitigación de riesgo.

  • Generar informes en tiempo real y tableros ejecutivos, ofreciendo visibilidad clara en indicadores clave de riesgo, el estado de los esfuerzos de evaluación y el perfil de riesgo general de la organización.

  • Integrar los datos y procesos de administración de riesgo en la administración de cumplimiento de normas y las iniciativas de gobierno y control corporativo.

Versión de la solución: 4
Solution.d2p1:Name: Administración de riesgos
